  "prompt": "How much would it cost to build a website like Bayut.com?",
  "response": "The cost of building a website like Bayut.com (a real estate listing platform) can vary widely depending on several factors:\n\n1. Development Approach:\n- Custom development: $20,000 - $100,000\n- Platform-based solution: $5,000 - $30,000\n\n2. Key Features Affecting Cost:\n- Property listing system\n- Search and filter functionality\n- Map integration\n- User authentication\n- Payment gateway\n- Mobile responsiveness\n- Admin dashboard\n- Advanced features like virtual tours\n\n3. Cost Breakdown:\n- Front-end development: $5,000 - $15,000\n- Back-end development: $10,000 - $30,000\n- Database design: $3,000 - $10,000\n- Design and UI/UX: $5,000 - $15,000\n- Advanced features: $5,000 - $20,000\n\n4. Ongoing Costs:\n- Hosting: $50 - $500/month\n- Maintenance: $500 - $2,000/month\n- Domain: $10 - $50/year\n\n5. Alternative Options:\n- Pre-built real estate platforms\n- WordPress solutions with plugins\n- Cheaper development outsourcing\n\nExact costs depend on specific requirements, developer rates, and complexity.",
